200~Git is a powerful tool for version control and collaboration.

It allows multiple developers to work on the same codebase without interfering with each other's changes.

With Git, every change you make is tracked, making it easy to roll back if needed.

Branching in Git helps you manage different features or bug fixes separately.

A commit in Git represents a snapshot of your changes at a given point in time.

GitHub is a cloud-based platform where you can host your Git repositories.

The git push command sends your local commits to a remote repository like GitHub.

git pull is used to fetch changes from a remote repository and merge them into your local branch.

Git makes collaboration easy with features like pull requests and code reviews.

Good Git practices, like making small, frequent commits, ensure a smooth workflow.
